### Variable Definitions
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@adminSecret = change-me-to-another-long-random-string
@userEmail = hei.iloniaina@gmail.com
@adminEmail = ilorandrianasolo4@gmail.com
@password = Password123!

# =============================================================================
# HEALTH CHECK
# =============================================================================

### 1. Health Check [cite: 11]
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

# =============================================================================
# BOOTSTRAPPING & ADMIN ACTIONS
# =============================================================================

### 2. Create First Admin (Using Master Secret) [cite: 36, 37]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/create
x-admin-secret: {{adminSecret}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "System Admin",
  "fatherName": "Root",
  "motherName": "Kernel",
  "dateOfBirth": "1980-01-01",
  "placeOfBirth": "Data Center",
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Admin Login [cite: 23]
# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Save Admin Token
@adminToken = {{adminLogin.response.body.token}}

# =============================================================================
# USER LIFECYCLE
# =============================================================================

### 4. User Registration [cite: 12, 13]
# Note: This uses multipart/form-data for the ID photo [cite: 14, 18]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="fullName"

Jane Doe
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="fatherName"

John Doe
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="motherName"

Mary Doe
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="dateOfBirth"

1990-06-15
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="placeOfBirth"

Nairobi
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

{{userEmail}}
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

{{password}}
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="idPhoto"; filename="id.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./image.jpeg
--WebAppBoundary--

### 5. Attempt User Login (Should fail with 403 - PENDING) [cite: 24, 29]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{userEmail}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

# =============================================================================
# ADMIN REVIEW PROCESS
# =============================================================================

### 6. List Pending Identities [cite: 44, 45]
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/identities/pending?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 7. Get Specific User Details (Replace {id} with actual ID from step 6) [cite: 51, 52]
@userId = cmohuw54i0000vfxknr7mtjvq
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/identities/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 8. Approve User [cite: 53]
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/identities/{{userId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 9. OR Reject User (Comment out step 8 if testing rejection) [cite: 56, 57]
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/identities/{{userId}}/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "The uploaded photo does not clearly show the document."
}

# =============================================================================
# POST-APPROVAL ACCESS
# =============================================================================

### 10. User Login (Should now succeed) [cite: 26, 27]
# @name userLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{userEmail}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Save User Token
@userToken = {{userLogin.response.body.token}}

### 11. Get Current User Profile [cite: 31, 33]
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 12. Check Identity Status (Polling) [cite: 34, 35]
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user/status
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}